# Privacy Policy for Rozze

**Last Updated:** January 4, 2026

## 1. Introduction

Welcome to **Rozze** ("we," "our," or "us"). We respect your privacy and are committed to protecting your personal data. This privacy policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our mobile application (the "App"). Please read this privacy policy carefully. If you do not agree with the terms of this privacy policy, please do not access the application.

## 2. Information We Collect

We utilize Google Sign-In and Google Drive services to ensure that your journal entries remain private and under your control. We may collect and process the following data about you:

### A. Personal Data
When you sign in using Google, we collect basic profile information to authenticate you and facilitate the functionality of the App:
*   **Email Address:** Used for account identification and authentication.
*   **Name & Profile Picture:** Used to personalize your user interface.

### B. User Content
The App allows you to create journal entries which may include:
*   **Text Entries**
*   **Voice/Audio Recordings**
*   **Video Recordings**
*   **Mood Tracking Data**

**Important:** All your detailed journal entries (text, audio, video) are stored in your personal **Google Drive**. We do not store this content on our own servers. This ensures that you retain full ownership and control over your personal journal data.

### C. Device Permissions
To provide the full functionality of the App, we may request access to certain features on your mobile device. You can manage these permissions in your device settings at any time.

*   **Camera:** Used to record video journals.
*   **Microphone:** Used to record audio for video journals and voice entries.
*   **Photo Library:** Used to allow you to upload images or videos to your journal contextually, or to suggest memories based on your photos.
*   **Location:** We use your location data *only locally* to suggest journaling topics based on places you have visited (e.g., "How was your trip to Central Park?"). We do not track or store your location history on our servers.
*   **Face ID / Biometrics:** Used locally to lock the App and keep your journal entries private from others who might handle your phone.

## 3. How We Use Your Information

We use the information we collect for the following purposes:
*   **To Provide the Service:** To authenticate you, manage your account, and enable you to create and save journal entries.
*   **To Improve the App:** To understand how users interact with the App and to identify and fix crashes (using Firebase Crashlytics).
*   **To Personalize Experience:** To provide content recommendations and memory prompts based on your context.

## 4. Where Your Data is Stored

*   **Journal Content:** Your actual journal data is stored securely in your own personal **Google Drive** account. We access this data via the Google Drive API only to display it to you within the App. We do not have access to read your journals outside of the App's automated function.
*   **App Metadata:** We may use **Google Firebase** to store basic user settings, preferences, and anonymous analytics data.

## 5. Third-Party Services

We may share information with or use the following third-party services that help us operate the App:
*   **Google Sign-In:** For authentication.
*   **Google Drive API:** For data storage.
*   **Firebase / Google Analytics:** For analyzing App usage and performance.
*   **RevenueCat (if applicable):** For managing subscriptions and purchases.

These third parties have access to your Personal Data only to perform these tasks on our behalf and are obligated not to disclose or use it for any other purpose.

## 6. Data Security

We use administrative, technical, and physical security measures to help protect your personal information. Since your data is primarily stored in your own Google Drive, it benefits from Google's world-class security infrastructure. However, please be aware that no security measures are perfect or impenetrable, and no method of data transmission can be guaranteed against any interception or other type of misuse.

## 7. Policy for Children

We do not knowingly solicit information from or market to children under the age of 13. If you become aware of any data we have collected from children under age 13, please contact us using the contact information provided below.

## 8. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time in order to reflect, for example, changes to our practices or for other operational, legal, or regulatory reasons. We will notify you of any changes by updating the "Last Updated" date of this Privacy Policy. You are advised to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any changes.

## 9. Contact Us

If you have questions or comments about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at:

